	<p class="ArticleContent" align="center"><font style="color:#000080;font-weight:bold;font-size:18px;font-family:Verdana, Arial, sans-serif;">2022 Horse-riding Games for March 8 International Women&#039;s Day Held</font></p><p class="ArticleContent" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph">&nbsp;</p><p class="ArticleContent" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph">There were 2022 horse-riding games for marking the March 8 International Women&#039;s Day in Pyongyang on Tuesday.</p><p class="ArticleContent" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph">Among the spectators were Choe Ryong Hae, Jo Yong Won, Ri Il Hwan, Ju Chang Il, Ri Tu Song and other senior Party and government officials and their wives.</p><p class="ArticleContent" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph">Pak Myong Sun, Kim Yo Jong and other women officials of the Central Committee of the Workers&#039; Party of Korea, officials of the C.C., Socialist Women&#039;s Union of Korea and women labor innovators and merited workers watched the games together with working people, youth and students in the city.</p><p class="ArticleContent" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph">Before the opening of the games, children entered on a chariot and gave bouquets of congratulations to exemplary women officials.</p><p class="ArticleContent" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph">Kim Il Guk, minister of Physical Culture and Sports, made an opening address.</p><p class="ArticleContent" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph">Buglers and drummers in Koguryo warrior clothes announced the opening of the games.</p><p class="ArticleContent" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph">There were a demonstration horse-riding by horse riders of the Mirim Riding Club and a demonstration of equestrian feats by artistes of the National Acrobatic Troupe.</p><p class="ArticleContent" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph">The horse-riders formed numbers &quot;3.8&quot;. And various equestrian feats were shown by women acrobats.</p><p class="ArticleContent" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph">Demonstration equestrian performance caught particular interest of the spectators.</p><p class="ArticleContent" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph">Such opening rite was followed by horse-riding games.</p><p class="ArticleContent" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph">Horse-riding games by couples selected in Pyongyang City and provinces drew attention of the spectators. And there were 1600m rider race, 1600m men&#039;s amateur race and 1600m women&#039;s amateur race in the outdoor horse-riding tracks.</p><p class="ArticleContent" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph">There were also other colorful games which added to the delight of the spectators.</p><p class="ArticleContent" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph">Players who came on the top standings were awarded cups, medals, certificates and prizes.</p><p class="ArticleContent" style="text-align:justify;text-justify:inter-ideograph">The games were followed by a congratulatory art performance.</p><p class="ArticleContent" align="right">Rodong Sinmun</p>	</td>
